      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Every category <strong>embeds fully and faithfully</strong> into its presheaf category [C<sup>op</sup>, Set]. The Yoneda embedding Y sends each object <em>a</em> to its hom-functor C(a, &ndash;), and no information is lost: distinct morphisms stay distinct, and every natural transformation between hom-functors comes from a morphism in C.</p>
